Sho Madjozi during her Press Conference at InterContinental Hotel O.R Tambo Airport on July 01, 2019 in Johannesburg, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - Sho Madjozi has returned to South Africa after winning the Best New International Act at the BET Awards in Los Angeles. The musician was welcomed by family, fans and Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa when she landed at OR Tambo in Johannesburg on Monday. READ: Sho Madjozi bags BET award Madjozi is the first female South African artist to claim the prestigious award following Sjava and Black Coffee's success. In her acceptance speech, Madjozi said her story was a testimony that dreams do come true. "My story is a testament that you can be from any village and any forgotten part of the world and you can still be a superstar", she said. Sho Madjozi's mom during her welcoming at O.R Tambo Airport on July 01, 2019 in Johannesburg, South Africa. Sho Madjozi arrived in SA after winning the Best New International Act at the 2019 BET Awards in Los Angeles. Sho Madjozi & Mom during her welcoming at O.R Tambo Airport on July 01, 2019 in Johannesburg, South Africa. Sho Madjozi arrived in SA after winning the Best New International Act at the 2019 BET Awards in Los Angeles. Sho Madjozi during her welcoming at O.R Tambo Airport on July 01, 2019 in Johannesburg, South Africa. Sho Madjozi arrived in SA after winning the Best New International Act at the 2019 BET Awards in Los Angeles. Sho Madjozi during her welcoming at O.R Tambo Airport on July 01, 2019 in Johannesburg, South Africa. Sho Madjozi arrived in SA after winning the Best New International Act at the 2019 BET Awards in Los Angeles.